This Mother’s Day, show some love for the mom in your life with:

Trying to decipher the mystery of baby wake windows? Owlet has your back! Our in-house sleep and newborn expert, Michelle Smith, has great advice for tackling baby wake windows.

1) They’re just a guideline - Wake windows are an idea of what to expect, but it’s ok if your happy and healthy baby isn’t quite following them.
2) They help avoid an overtired baby - When you’re coming to the close of your baby’s wake window, follow their cues to avoid making them too tired.
3) They’re subject to change - With age, growth, milestones, teething and even illness, you’ll find that your baby’s wake windows will slightly change and sometimes not so slightly.

Check out this handy table of suggested baby wake windows and read more of Michelle’s insight on our blog, linked in our stories.
